text:
we present our first story this year: #pttmerdeka19 before #valentinesday (not all love stories are lovely). "dear you, from an npd survivor who was agonizing in dating hell" by risma, 23.  the beautiful moments we made slowly faded away - his brilliance, kind-hearted, caring, and supportive manner evaporated into someone i never knew before: self-centered, careless, manipulative, lazy, and harsh. editors note: this is a true-story case of #npd (#narcissticpersonalitydisorder). this disorder ‘can last for years or be lifelong’. in english, read now link in bio: http://www.bit.ly/pttmerdeka19-1
-
illustrated by @futile_odds
-
do you have your honest story to share? submit via www.perempuantagartegar.online/kontak
-
info: the reason why we don't mind receiving stories in english or bahasa indonesia is because we also want to bring forth the dialogues of #femaleequality to #metoo of indonesia to the world. knowing that we're not silent. knowing they can also feel our pain and gain from it.

text_retweet:
reposted from @backto_muslimidentity -  perempuan butuh syariat islam, bukan ruu pks
.
pengamat politik dan pemerhati perempuan, pratama julia sunjandari, menilai alasan tingginya angka kekerasan seksual di indonesia yang menjadi latar belakang legalisasi rancangan undang undang (ruu) penghapusan kekerasan seksual (pks) sungguh mengada-ada.

pasalnya, menurut pratma, bukan sekadar ada umbrella act lalu persoalan kekerasan seksual selesai. perancis yang telah mengatur tentang sanksi kriminal pelecehan seksual di tempat kerja menunjukkan pejabat dunia christine lagarde yang juga mantan menkeu pransis pernah menjadi korban pelecehan seksual bersama puluhan mantan perempuan terkemuka prancis lainnya. atau gerakan #metoo yang kini mendunia menunjukkan bahwa hukum di negara-negara tersebut tidak mampu menghentikan kekerasan seksual.

pratma lalu mengungkap tiga alasan kalangan feminis ngotot ingin melegalisasi ruu pks, “pertama menyuburkan perilaku sekuler liberal. muatan srhr (sexual and reproductive healths rights) sebagai ‘amanah’ beijing platform for action (bpfa) amat kuat. frasa ‘kontrol seksual’ itu menegaskan daulat atas tubuh sehingga seorang istri berhak menolak hamil atau menolak ajakan suaminya ke tempat tidur. termasuk hak untuk meluapkan orientasi seksual pada apapun atau siapapun.” kedua, kata pratma julia, merusak keluarga terutama relasi suami istri. tak ada lagi qawwam (pemimpin) dalam rumah tangga termasuk dalam hubungan yang amat privat. ketiga, menikam syariat islam. kalangan liberal, dengan dukungan negara leluasa mengadvokasi umat untuk tidak lagi patuh pada hukum allah. “menjadi keharusan bagi kaum muslimin untuk menolak dan mencegah kemunkaran ini dengan aksi nyata,” ungkapnya kepada mnews, rabu (30/1/2019). pratma kemudian menjelaskan bahwa umat islam harus berupaya menegakkan syariat islam kaffah sebagai solusi persoalan kekerasan terhadap perempuan, “tidak kalah penting mengedukasi umat bahwa persoalan kekerasan seksual, bahkan pelecehan kehormatan perempuan tak akan terjadi jika khilafah tegak. syariat kaffah itu memiliki hukum yang amat memuliakan manusia apalagi perempuan dengan hukum-hukum sistem pergaulannya,” tukasnya.[]

pasalnya, menurut pratma, bukan sekadar ada umbrella act lalu persoalan kekerasan seksual selesai. perancis yang telah mengatur tentang sanksi kriminal pelecehan seksual di tempat kerja menunjukkan pejabat dunia christine lagarde yang juga mantan menkeu pransis pernah menjadi korban pelecehan seksual bersama puluhan mantan perempuan terkemuka prancis lainnya. atau gerakan #metoo yang kini mendunia menunjukkan bahwa hukum di negara-negara tersebut tidak mampu menghentikan kekerasan seksual.

pratma lalu mengungkap tiga alasan kalangan feminis ngotot ingin melegalisasi ruu pks, “pertama menyuburkan perilaku sekuler liberal. muatan srhr (sexual and reproductive healths rights) sebagai ‘amanah’ beijing platform for action (bpfa) amat kuat. frasa ‘kontrol seksual’ itu menegaskan daulat atas tubuh sehingga seorang istri berhak menolak hamil atau menolak ajakan suaminya ke tempat tidur. termasuk hak untuk meluapkan orientasi seksual pada apapun atau siapapun.” kedua, kata pratma julia, merusak keluarga terutama relasi suami istri. tak ada lagi qawwam (pemimpin) dalam rumah tangga termasuk dalam hubungan yang amat privat. ketiga, menikam syariat islam. kalangan liberal, dengan dukungan negara leluasa mengadvokasi umat untuk tidak lagi patuh pada hukum allah. “menjadi keharusan bagi kaum muslimin untuk menolak dan mencegah kemunkaran ini dengan aksi nyata,” ungkapnya kepada mnews, rabu (30/1/2019). pratma kemudian menjelaskan bahwa umat islam harus berupaya menegakkan syariat islam kaffah sebagai solusi persoalan kekerasan terhadap perempuan, “tidak kalah penting mengedukasi umat bahwa persoalan kekerasan seksual, bahkan pelecehan kehormatan perempuan tak akan terjadi jika khilafah tegak. syariat kaffah itu memiliki hukum yang amat memuliakan manusia apalagi perempuan dengan hukum-hukum sistem pergaulannya,” tukasnya.[]

text_retweet:
reposted from @mz_juanita1 -  my empowerment story is one that has involved so many women, sisters, friends.
my story is incomplete without acknowledging the key role every book written played, how their videos /messages changed my mindset , their biographies made me believe in a world of possibilities , their quotes changed the narrative , their support gave me strength to push forward , their passion fueled my passion and so much more.
my empowerment began with a mother who had to deal with a baby girl who had a very low self esteem, so many people would never believe i was that baby girl because her labor of love groomed me into a confident lady although it was a long process and until she was certain i knew my value as a woman she never stopped and she is still pushing the bar till this day. 
growing up the likes of juanita bynum, katheryn khulman and maya angelou planted seeds through their messages and books that i believe set me on my greatness journey, my soul sisters from different locations have been a blessing in my empowerment journey.
role models like @funtoibuoye, @folusog @ibukunawosika @mmwithnimi @ffadejumo @bekesbukola @cpyfamily @stephanielinus @temitope_olagbegi @theodoraayeni @taiyeapata @okojie.ofubella @mercychinwo @taradurotoye @toluijogun , barely seen most of them but in being themselves and living authentic have been a blessing to me, i can say these women are empowered and their lives have been a source of inspiration to me in dark moments. the major turning point in my empowerment journey was in 2017 when i stumbled on jumoke adenowo's @jumokeadenowo interview on the king woman series(i think every woman should watch the kingwoman series by @kemiadetiba), she spoke with so much power, exuded confidence but yet so calm. i didn't even know how multi dimensional this woman was but her authenticity drew me like iron to magnet. i searched for everything i could lay my hands on that had to do with her from posts, youtube messages practically every thing that had @jumokeadenowo i had to see, read, listen and i am still very much intrigued by this great woman and this resulted in a major paradigm shift in my life. 
#empoweredwomenempoweroth

text:
"maria with barbara" stiff motion.

postures, gestures, movements and figures... time of study. working in a new pice!! 😁
working on a new piece but i really hope to show you some photos of my last site specific artwork that evolve from this series of photographs from the performance. 
at this stage of the body of work the lights take importance and we created a purplish atmosphere through them.

in this ongoing body of work the main concepts are: body distortions, body extensions and personal space. explored through photography, performance and site specific installation with a series of sellotape sculptural garments.  collaboration work with @intoxication_relation as a living sculpture. .

text:
wylie said that bannon's plans began to solidify in 2014, when cambridge analytica consulted various republican campaigns and pacs ahead of the midterm elections. the company began to test and apply its psychographics by using facebook data to model individuals' personality types in order to understand how to influence them.

documents show the john bolton super pac, which promoted candidates supported by recently appointed white house national security adviser john bolton, paid cambridge analytical $454,700 in 2014 for "behavioral microtargeting with psychographic messaging." those services included strategies that broke individual voters into "clusters" based on what messages would resonate with them.

wylie also said the company used focus groups and messaging trials in 2014 to test some of the concepts that became core themes of the trump campaign, such as "drain the swamp" and imagery of walls. "a lot of the narratives of the trump campaign were what we were testing in 2014," wylie said.

he added that bannon directly presided over much of the company's initial research. "everything that we were doing ultimately had to be passed up to bannon for approval," said wylie, who left the company in late 2014.

wylie said bannon would fly to london about once a month for company meetings, and during that time he came to understand bannon's ideology. "he really liked the idea of using a military-style approach to changing people's perceptions," wylie said.

curt devine, donie o'sullivan & drew griffin
cnn

wylie said that bannon's plans began to solidify in 2014, when cambridge analytica consulted various republican campaigns and pacs ahead of the midterm elections. the company began to test and apply its psychographics by using facebook data to model individuals' personality types in order to understand how to influence them.

documents show the john bolton super pac, which promoted candidates supported by recently appointed white house national security adviser john bolton, paid cambridge analytical $454,700 in 2014 for "behavioral microtargeting with psychographic messaging." those services included strategies that broke individual voters into "clusters" based on what messages would resonate with them.

he added that bannon directly presided over much of the company's initial research. "everything that we were doing ultimately had to be passed up to bannon for approval," said wylie, who left the company in late 2014.

wylie said bannon would fly to london about once a month for company meetings, and during that time he came to understand bannon's ideology. "he really liked the idea of using a military-style approach to changing people's perceptions," wylie said.

text:
- bannon got it immediately. he believes in the whole andrew breitbart doctrine that politics is downstream from culture, so to change politics you need to change culture. and fashion trends are a useful proxy for that. trump is like a pair of uggs, or crocs, basically. so how do you get from people thinking ‘ugh. totally ugly’ to the moment when everyone is wearing them? that was the inflection point he was looking for.

is what cambridge analytica does akin to bullying? - i think it’s worse than bullying, christopher wylie says. - because people don’t necessarily know it’s being done to them. at least bullying respects the agency of people because they know. so it’s worse, because if you do not respect the agency of people, anything that you’re doing after that point is not conducive to a democracy. and fundamentally, information warfare is not conducive to democracy.

millions of people’s personal information was stolen and used to target them in ways they wouldn’t have seen, and couldn’t have known about, by a mercenary outfit, cambridge analytica, who, wylie says, “would work for anyone”. who would pitch to russian oil companies. would they subvert elections abroad on behalf of foreign governments?

it occurs to me to ask wylie this one night. - yes.

nato or non-nato? - either. i mean they’re mercenaries. they’ll work for pretty much anyone who pays.

it’s an incredible revelation. it also encapsulates all of the problems of outsourcing – at a global scale, with added cyberweapons. and in the middle of it all are the public – our intimate family connections, our “likes”, our crumbs of personal data, all sucked into a swirling black hole that’s expanding and growing and is now owned by a politically motivated billionaire.

carole cadwalladr
the guardian

text:
what an extraordinary time to be a woman. with the #metoo movement we have seen the sweeping impact of women supporting each other on an issue that is blind to status and income, that moves across geographical and cultural borders. online platforms have nurtured loyal communities of interested women who embrace such spaces for honest discussion on both big and small issues related to everyday life (@manrepeller) and career (@girlboss, @forbeswomen). here, they find courage in one another to touch on subjects that may reveal them as less than perfect, to harness tools and advise for self-realisation, and to demand change to environments that doesn’t allow them to progress and advance. at the same time, a plethora of woman-led businesses work to facilitate the success of other women by providing access to venture capital, and safe entrepreneurial hubs (@thewing). it is this new mindset that excites us. there's a growing mindfulness that our decisions matter in the greater scheme of things, as individuals and as a collective force, and it’s translating into the way we live.  it’s making us revisit the why’s and how’s when shopping, when starting and running our businesses, when raising our children, etc. - and it’s something we attach a certain pride to. it’s not surprising that women are at the forefront of bold climate leadership around the world. 
at therim, we are mothers, entrepreneurs, un veterans, and we want to create a space for informal and untimid conversations about sustainability in context of our everyday life. there's a certain pressure when we talk about a "conscious lifestyle"; too often it's still associated with privilege and it can be a hustle to navigate the vast information surrounding the subjects at hand. we believe that women hold the power to push through the changes needed to beat climate change and ensure the transition towards a healthy, livable future.

#womenwillchangetheworld #consciouswomen #incrediblewomen #girlboss #sustainability

text:
one of my online clients is up in the midlands and we were having our weekly check in last week and this is basically what i ended up saying. (it’s really powerful and a very common behavioural trait of the binge eater so i hope it helps) “nothing in life is perfect, so stop trying to make it that way. find the joy in doing the best you can, then leave it at that.

your perfectionist mindset stresses about trying to do everything perfectly, trying to dot all the i's and cross all the t's and when you can't do this, shit hits the fan.

then you end up placing more pressure on yourself, and question why cant i do this. you are then even harder on yourself, try to sum up even more willpower and strive even more to make things 'perfect'. as you can see it is a vicious cycles that has been a massive contributor to your unhappiness, low self esteem and a feeling of self doubt.” now i’m sure many of you reading this can relate to this problem right?

so what if i told you you could change things almost instantly and start making some real progress as of today... well you can!

the solution.... the first thing is actually recognising and accepting that your approach of 'perfect' isn't working that great so it's time for a re-think.

the second - taking action in a more moderate way.

think about it - you'll get more success doing something 70-80% of the time for the majority of your life than you will doing something at 100% for 1 or 2 weeks - getting overwhelmed - quitting and then repeating that cycle.

something to think about because it’s very relevant to all areas of your life, not just food, but work and life and relationships too.

text:
cześć :) 27 lutego swoją premierę będzie miała pozycja "vox". autorka christina dalcher stworzyła dystopię, w której rząd amerykański wydaje dekret, w którym kobietom wolno wypowiedzieć tylko 100 słów dziennie. na początek. później wszystkie kobiety tracą prawa do wykonywania zawodu, czytania i pisania.

wyobrażacie sobie taką sytuację? ja nie i nasza główna bohaterka, która większość życia poświęciła badaniom naukowym też nie i uświadamia sobie, że musi stanąć w obronie kobiet.

lubię tego rodzaju lektury, chociaż nie wyobrażam sobie, żebyśmy cofnęli się do takiego momentu, w którym kobietom odbiera się wszystkie podstawowe dzisiaj prawa. dlatego lekturę tej pozycji traktuje jako ciekawostkę, a nie przestrogę. :) ale siłą rzeczy zaczęłam się zastanawiać, gdybym miała do dyspozycji dziennie tylko 100 słów. jakbym je wykorzystała? np. główna bohaterka zawsze zostawia jedno słowo na koniec dnia - "dobranoc" dla swojej córki 🎈

myślę, że moje słowa to w większości też byłyby wyrażane uczucia i emocje do najbliższych.  ewentualnie słowa mocno wyważone, które w jakiś sposób mogłyby coś zmienić...
__________________________

name: Dagmara Sobczak
tweet_full:
cześć :) 27 lutego swoją premierę będzie miała pozycja "vox". autorka christina dalcher stworzyła dystopię, w której rząd amerykański wydaje dekret, w którym kobietom wolno wypowiedzieć tylko 100 słów dziennie. na początek. później wszystkie kobiety tracą prawa do wykonywania zawodu, czytania i pisania.

wyobrażacie sobie taką sytuację? ja nie i nasza główna bohaterka, która większość życia poświęciła badaniom naukowym też nie i uświadamia sobie, że musi stanąć w obronie kobiet.

lubię tego rodzaju lektury, chociaż nie wyobrażam sobie, żebyśmy cofnęli się do takiego momentu, w którym kobietom odbiera się wszystkie podstawowe dzisiaj prawa. dlatego lekturę tej pozycji traktuje jako ciekawostkę, a nie przestrogę. :) ale siłą rzeczy zaczęłam się zastanawiać, gdybym miała do dyspozycji dziennie tylko 100 słów. jakbym je wykorzystała? np. główna bohaterka zawsze zostawia jedno słowo na koniec dnia - "dobranoc" dla swojej córki 🎈

myślę, że moje słowa to w większości też byłyby wyrażane uczucia i emocje do najbliższych.  ewentualnie słowa mocno wyważone, które w jakiś sposób mogłyby coś zmienić...

text:
- this was steve bannon's baby, said former contractor christopher wylie, who described cambridge analytica as "bannon's arsenal of weaponry to wage a culture war on america using military strategies."
.
bannon wanted to use the sorts of aggressive messaging tactics usually reserved for geopolitical conflicts to move the us electorate further to the right, wylie said. he had already directed a series of anti-establishment, conservative documentary films and presided over the far-right website breitbart news, but cambridge analytica would mark another step in his overall ambitions to transform the nation.

with financial backing from hedge-fund billionaire robert mercer, bannon co-founded cambridge analytica in 2013 as the us-branch of strategic communication laboratories (scl) group, a british company that advertises how it has conducted "behavioral change" programs in more than 60 countries.

wylie described cambridge analytica as - steve bannon and robert mercer using a foreign, military contractor ... to use some of the same techniques that the military uses ... on the american electorate.

curt devine, donie o'sullivan and drew griffin
cnn

text:
u.s. president donald trump's former aide steve bannon sought to use personal information collected online to promote "a culture war," a whistleblower on now-defunct political data firm cambridge analytica told u.s. senators on wednesday.

bannon, a former cambridge analytica vice president, "saw cultural warfare as a means to create enduring change in american politics," testified christopher wylie, who says information about tens of millions of facebook users ended up in cambridge analytica's hands.

bannon's attorney william burck did not immediately respond to an email request for comment on wylie's testimony.

wylie, who worked for scl, the british-based parent of cambridge analytica, told the senate judiciary committee that cambridge analytica hired hackers to collect data it then used against opponents of its political clients.

allegations of the improper use of data for 87 million facebook users by cambridge analytica, which was hired by trump's 2016 election campaign, have led to investigations in the united states and europe.

mark hosenball
reuters

text: в роскошное время мы живём, господа! сначала prada, затем gucci, а теперь ketty perry подверглись суровой критике со стороны модной общественности, нечаянно процитировав в своих творениях блекфейс (разновидность театрального грима, который использовался комиками для своих шоу и водевилей в первой половине 20 в. и представлял собой карикатурное изображение лица чернокожего человека). напрасно бедняжка кэти перри попыталась оправдаться, мол, лоферы из чёрной кожи с глазами и красными губами выпускались ещё в девяти цветах. модель чёрного цвета вынудили снять с продажи. всего несколько дней назад gucci, оказавшись в точно такой же ситуации, даже оправдываться не стали и тоже сняли с продажи свитер с прорезью на горловине, которая имитирует рот с красными губами. но самое, на мой взгляд, бредовое обвинение досталось prada. в середине декабря они выпустили фигурки безобидных обезьянок с большими красными губами, которые тут же признали расистскими. prada, понятно, тут же принесли свои извинения, заявив, что эти обезьянки — фантазийные персонажи и не имеют ничего общего с реальным миром. но из магазинов фигурки все-таки изъяли. вывод напрашивается сам собой: чрезмерный загар, красные губы и любое упоминание обезьянок отныне может быть чревато и для каждого из них нас. один дизайнер в твиттере так и написал: «ок, давайте просто сделаем правилом, что любой человек, не являющийся афроамериканцем, не будет создавать, продвигать и вообще вспоминать  комбинацию чёрный + лицо». хорошо, что мою любимую иконку #рукалицо пока никто не запретил, даже если она по-расистски  загорелая 🤦🏾‍♀️ #скандалы #интриги #fashionismydrug
name: Ирина Суханова

text:
how many of you ladies have faced trauma or hardship  in korea, how many of you have a story to share or a desire to grow a strong female  expat support system? 
this is how i feel having heard too many women's stories in rhe last year it is time to start taking action  as one group.

my storytelling  journey  in korea began a few years ago after facing my own trauma in korea. since then i joined a global social media project  halfthestory that has helped me a lot to gain the courage to speak up about so much more than just my own struggles in korea. 
i know focus on expat women and the social and cultural  struggles that they face here in korea. 
many of you have already shared your own stories with me and shared them with the half the story project and i am so incredibly proud of you all for having the courage to do so. 
now is the time in korea  for woman to truly come together  and make waves of change.
i can feel it already. 
now is the time for you to  share those stories and let them be heard.

sharing struggles  leads to awareness  awareness  leads to action and action leads to change ♡ 
if you want your story  to be heard  or have a female friend in korea in need of support  please connect with me via dm. .
.
.
.
. .

text:
inzingubo designs is proud to be associated with turning point. 
turning point is a programme that is derived from the recently launched #metoo initiative. 
as an empowering organisation we support woman who have and are currently going through any physical, emotional or mental trauma. its also an organisation that brings ladies together to empower them to face the daily hurdles in life. formed out of the #metoo campaigns we give ladies a turning point in their lifes for the better! 
turning point will be launching across the country over time. so keep an eye out for your area. 
ladies of the south we hope to see you at the launch on the 16th march. 
inzingubo designs will be present. come meet us.

text:
💔menendez brothers erik and lyle have been in prison for almost 30 years now! this is an interview they did a long time ago with barbara walters. i didn’t like this interview because instead of having compassion for sexual abuse victims she made snarky remarks for drama. she did the same thing with corey feldman who said he was sexually abused as well, and during the interview she pretty much made it sound like he was a liar....until the police confirmed that he made a call and reported it a long time ago. why is it so hard to believe that men/boys also get sexually abused? why is it so hard to have compassion? we tend to condemn people before finding out all the facts by reading news headlines. the menendez brothers family and friends say that they are telling the truth and that horrible things were happening in that family.
⠀
💔the menendez brothers sexual abuse evidence was not allowed during their second trial by the judge! the justice system failed them! they are serving life in prison without the possibility of parole. please help them get a new trial by signing the petition on change.org (link in bio). it just needs your signature.
⠀
📍please let the government, the state of california, and the world know that we want changes! sexual abuse evidence should have been allowed during the menendez brothers second trial.
⠀
📍i will put as much financial backing as i can into this petition even if it’s just $1 here $20 there to promote it for as long as i can. i just ask for your signature of support on the petition. thank you so very much to those of you who have already signed and to all those who support menendez brothers freedom. thank you guys! with every single signature i feel so much hope and happiness that this situation will have a positive outcome/change. ♥️
⠀
❗️#freemenendezbrothers ❗️
⠀
📍please share this information! thank you!

text:
“i just get along better with guys” 🌬

something i used to say a lot. and something i hear a lot of girls say, especially when guys are around.

i thought it to be true for myself for a long time, not realising that whenever i said this particular phrase i was actually implying that i’m not ‘one of these girls’. not someone to wear lots of makeup, freak out when a nail is broken or gossip 24/7 about other girls. and whilst that is true, and whilst it is true that a big part of my friends used to be (and are) male, i recently got aware of this saying.
why? 
i think @stella.rae made a better job at explaining this on her podcast but in summary: whenever girls say that they ‘just get along better with guys’ it portraits girls as being superficial, too emotional, annoying even. 
and i know this to not be true. i am surrounded by beautiful girls. truly beautiful. in fact i’ve been traveling with two gorgeous souls the past weeks. girls who have gone through a lot and who still know how to be compassionate, funny, independent. who fart and snore and eat melted chocolate and wear big loop ear rings and sweat pants and tight dresses. 
and no. i don’t ‚just get along better with guys‘ because i’ve been proven over and over again that having (both male and) female friends is fucking worth while. wearing fake lashes is cool, wearing worn down sneakers is cool. some girls like beer, others only rosé. some neither. and that is just fine as it is. 
have you ever said that you just like male friends better? if so, reflect on why you did so and if the underlying cause might be unconscious misogyny?
let me know what you think, i know this might be controversial. but i like controversy. 
much love 
#femaleempowerment#friendship#soulsisters

text:
former u.s. national security adviser michael flynn admitted on friday that he asked russia to delay a u.n. vote seen as damaging to israel, but diplomats said it was not the only country he and presidential adviser jared kushner lobbied.

in the hours before the vote by the 15-member united nations security council on dec. 23, flynn also phoned the u.n. missions of uruguay and malaysia, and kushner spoke with kim darroch, the british ambassador to the united states, according to diplomats familiar with the conversations, who spoke on condition of anonymity.

the lobbying took place before republican president donald trump, who was known for his pro-israel campaign rhetoric, took office on jan. 20. it failed, with the security council adopting a resolution demanding an end to israeli settlement building on land palestinians want for an independent state. the vote was 14 in favor and one abstention by the united states.

the efforts made on israel's behalf capped several days of unusual diplomacy. in a surprise dec. 21 move, egypt had called for a vote the next day on the draft resolution, prompting both trump and israel to urge washington to veto the text.

a senior israeli official told reuters that israeli officials contacted trump's transition team at a "high level" to ask for help after failing to persuade democratic president barack obama's administration to veto the draft u.n. resolution.

according to court documents made public on friday, a member of trump's presidential transition team, later identified by sources as trump's son-in-law kushner, told flynn on dec. 22 to contact officials from foreign governments, including russia, to convince them to delay the vote or veto the resolution.

flynn spoke with then-russian ambassador to the united states sergei kislyak that day, and again the following day, according to the court documents.

michelle nichols
reuters

former u.s. national security adviser michael flynn admitted on friday that he asked russia to delay a u.n. vote seen as damaging to israel, but diplomats said it was not the only country he and presidential adviser jared kushner lobbied.

in the hours before the vote by the 15-member united nations security council on dec. 23, flynn also phoned the u.n. missions of uruguay and malaysia, and kushner spoke with kim darroch, the british ambassador to the united states, according to diplomats familiar with the conversations, who spoke on condition of anonymity.

the lobbying took place before republican president donald trump, who was known for his pro-israel campaign rhetoric, took office on jan. 20. it failed, with the security council adopting a resolution demanding an end to israeli settlement building on land palestinians want for an independent state. the vote was 14 in favor and one abstention by the united states.

the efforts made on israel's behalf capped several days of unusual diplomacy. in a surprise dec. 21 move, egypt had called for a vote the next day on the draft resolution, prompting both trump and israel to urge washington to veto the text.

a senior israeli official told reuters that israeli officials contacted trump's transition team at a "high level" to ask for help after failing to persuade democratic president barack obama's administration to veto the draft u.n. resolution.

according to court documents made public on friday, a member of trump's presidential transition team, later identified by sources as trump's son-in-law kushner, told flynn on dec. 22 to contact officials from foreign governments, including russia, to convince them to delay the vote or veto the resolution.

flynn spoke with then-russian ambassador to the united states sergei kislyak that day, and again the following day, according to the court documents.

michelle nichols
reuters

okay, i’m about to get very open, honest and vulnerable and that is a challenge for me but i hope that this rawness will help to inspire other women out there feeling insecure today.
so, as y’all are (hopefully) aware...people these says have all time high anxiety. thankfully mine has been bearable recently and i haven’t had to use any medication for months❣️ #yaaas
☀️for all you ladies out there going through the deep waters, sticking it out, i just wanted to say; girl, you are not alone. as a teacher i see so many students (particularly my young girls... although the boys hide it all and that’s a whole other story) who think they need to be perfect. it’s a commonality for me to have to stop lessons to talk with an individual to say, “oh honey, your makeup is lovely! put that mascara down and get to work.❣️”. i then have to regurgitate some form of this increasingly familiar pep talk in order to get the student back on track. it’s a pep talk i sometimes tell myself, too.... it goes like⤵️
☀️”girl, you got this.”, “you don’t need that much makeup.”, “you’re perfectly imperfect; own your natural beauty.” , etc.
☀️in the age of social medias, comparing yourself to that perfectly airbrushed, filtered, 1% body fat influencer or celebrity is all the more in yo’ face. i have to admit i am so guilty of the filters and poses and not owning my own (i’m gonna call it) socially perceived imperfections...... so, i wanted to #getrealyall❣️
☀️here’s a little comparison for you. #instame vs. #realme on the same tuesday.
☀️are you that girl treadin’ those waters, obsessed with being the barbie society wants you to be? struggle bussin’ with self-esteem? #metoo ...
☀️let’s  #nancypelosi 👏👏👏👏👏to the larger society’s beauty standards today. be empowered tonight and each night as you fall asleep. and as always, remember you can get through those waters just as you got through the waves on your journey to them. remember you are #juststrong not #foragirl ❣️❣️❣️❣️❣

text:
i want you all to know that i haven't forgotten about my survivor of the week series. i have been taking another social media break as i have been pondering whether or not i want to continue with my legal case against my rapist. i am so honored and humbled that people feel compelled and safe enough to send me their stories and i promise to keep sharing them.
leave drop a 🖤 in the comments to show this incredible survivor some support.
•••
the survivor of the week series is a space for survivors to publically or anonymously share their stories, artwork, poetry and other content relating to sexual assault, domestic violence and other forms of interpersonal violence. the mission of this series is showcase and support survivors in a safe space. submissions are accepted at survivoroftheweek@gmail.com and if you wish to submit anonymously put confidential in the subject line.

rp @earthlove777 --- farmers and shepherds on the italian island of sardinia have been pouring their milk away, saying they would rather destroy it than sell it for next to nothing.
the price of sheep milk has dropped more than 25 per cent to 60 cents a litre following a fall in the price of pecorino romano cheese, which absorbs about half the island’s sheep milk production. (euronews.com) rp @donnamaria1961 @light.knowledge.power could this be the beginning of the end?
italian farmers dump milk in protest against low prices.
could this be the impact of the rise of veganism and great demand for vegan milk, cheese etc? 
could this be the beginning of the end of the dairy industry in the eu? let's wait and see.

text:
fb memory popped up today from 2 years ago...
.

trying to find the words to truly express how i feel... last night i was out with some girlfriends, having a pleasant girls' night. an acquaintance of my friend was encouraged to dance with me. i told him i was not a touchy feely person and i didn't want to dance and he preceded to pick me up over his shoulder and carry me to the dance floor. i yelled the whole time he carried me to put me down and as soon as he did i walked back to my friends, leaving him on the dance floor. he followed me back. continued to touch me, to grab my hands and try to dance. i stood strong and told him to stop, that i don't like being touched. one of my friends told him to stop and he replied he "hadn't even started yet" then he grabbed me from behind and began to kiss on my ear and neck. i elbowed myself free, put my hand up and said "stop" straight to his face. i was in tears. this wasn't ok. i had said numerous times i was uncomfortable, that i didn't want to be touched and he kept coming at me. how frustrating for a woman to have to continue to say no, stop and be completely ignored. he tried to come and apologize but i said i didn't want to hear it and to leave me alone. how ridiculous that you have to bring a woman to tears before you hear her words. his actions were not ok, i was clear from the beginning that i was not interested. my mind is swirling from this man's rude ignorance. #nomeansno #respectwomen #metoo #metoomovement #survivor #iamstrong #respect #notmychoicemyfirsttime

text:
u.s. president donald trump's former aide steve bannon sought to use personal information collected online to promote "a culture war," a whistleblower on now-defunct political data firm cambridge analytica told u.s. senators on wednesday.

bannon, a former cambridge analytica vice president, "saw cultural warfare as a means to create enduring change in american politics," testified christopher wylie, who says information about tens of millions of facebook users ended up in cambridge analytica's hands.

bannon's attorney william burck did not immediately respond to an email request for comment on wylie's testimony.

wylie, who worked for scl, the british-based parent of cambridge analytica, told the senate judiciary committee that cambridge analytica hired hackers to collect data it then used against opponents of its political clients.

allegations of the improper use of data for 87 million facebook users by cambridge analytica, which was hired by trump's 2016 election campaign, have led to investigations in the united states and europe.

mark hosenball
reuters

text:
​​#историичитателей

второй день не могу прийти в себя от истории с нападением на беременную молодую женщину. плачу. и боюсь. в моей жизни - муж, с которым мы любили друг друга с юности и ждали 7 лет, пока его родители нас поженят (сначала искали мужа золовке, выдали ее, потом ждали, пока она родит, чтобы сделать бешик-туй). и вот мы поженились. но что-то пошло не так уже в первый год семейной жизни. не было физического насилия, но психологическое - постоянно.

муж приходил поздно, я не знала, что делать (пытаясь сохранить приличия, не говорила своим родным, но подключала свекровь и ее многочисленных сестер, на что мне отвечали: "ни один молодой мужчина не будет после работы бежать под юбку жены. вот после 40 лет - да, может быть"). когда я узнала о своей беременности, свекровь, помню, плакала. на третьем месяце я ушла из их дома. почему? потому что более остро почувствовала холод, отстраненность мужа. еще через пару месяцев увезла свои вещи. меня не пытались оставить, но, правда, говорили - "раз уж твои родители так решили, печально, но ты оставайся. мы с тобой". дальше началась холодная война. я родила сына. на родах присутствовал муж (я ему позвонила. видимо, надеялась сохранить семью или боялась висеть на шее моих родителей, они тоже, признаюсь, не сахар). и еще через полгода я узнаю причины, по которым с мужем произошел разлад.

оказывается, после свадьбы он познакомился с женщиной старше, она влюбилась (ну или он влюбил ее в себя). они встречались, потом сделали никох и она забеременела (очень хотела/хотели ребенка). рожали мы, как выясняется, в одном месяце. потом он привел ее домой к родителям, она снова забеременела в прошлом году, родила (я уж надеялась, что наконец-то мне не придется с позором идти в махаллю и просить составить акт, и они сами там займутся разводом). но не тут-то было. та женщина ушла, подает на алименты.

я живу отдельно от родителей с сыном (ипотека). с мужем за эти пять лет так и не развелись (скажу честно, в месте, где я работаю, желательно не быть в разводе, или я себя так обманываю и во что-то еще верю, но по факту - в суд не ходила и муж тоже не ходил).

text:
it's been almost a year since i started working as a correspondent with @greatlakesbrewingnews
it's been twenty four hours since i discovered what a disturbing individual i was working for...my primal self has just submitted my resignation. i am a woman, & i am raising girls, and i can no longer stand behind or be associated with this publication. metzger said it himself, "one aggressive move and a man's career can derail.", well you've certainly done yourself and your newspaper in with this "aggressive move", & i am happy to cut my losses.
.
i've been part of the craft beer community for well over a year now and i've been so impressed by it's welcoming and encouraging nature, it does not surprise me to see it come together to stand up to an entitled individual who has the audacity to pour his filth onto paper and circulate it as "brewing news". some of us are parents, raising girls that we want to be treated better and never approached by a misogynistic pig such as the publisher of this paper and boys who will not be so neglected on their upbringing that they have to approach women in such a manner as to blame genetics or instincts. most of us are good people who just want and hold these standards for ourselves. sitting here this evening watching the disney movie brave with my husband and two daughters it finalized my decision to part ways with great lakes brewing news.
.
this has been a heavy topic on my mind all day and standing up for what i think is right by not backing a company that would publicize and make light of such a subject is my way of showing my daughters how to be brave. it can be intimidating to be in a generally viewed as "man's world" industry, and i was initially so excited to be working with a paper where i could bring beer news to the people, but i don't need their platform to do what i love, i can, and will do this on my own. look for your upcoming beer events here on my personal page and feel free to reach out to me to collaborate!

text:
wearing orange today in support of national teen dating violence awareness day. teen dating violence has shaped the person i am (for the worse), and continues to affect my life into my adult life. teen dating violence often happens when we are young, pliable, easily manipulated, and still developing our sense of selves and self esteem. it is very important to be a role model to children and young adults, to teach them what healthy relationships look like, and to be supportive to those who need help, whether they believe they need it or not. we need to not blame children and young adults for falling into the hands of abuse, as you never know their situation, and why they never left when things got bad. if anyone ever needs to reach out about a bad relationship and abuse, please feel free to reach out. i will listen, and i have been there many times❤❤❤
.
.
.

text:
#metoosday everything is bigger in texas...except for the sentencing and consequences for raping somebody. those are apparently so small, they're pretty much non-existent. this is jacob anderson, another rapist fraternity bro that gets to continue his privileged life with no interruption after violently sexually assaulting a girl at a party at ut dallas in 2016. the victim, like so many others before her, went through all the proper channels to report the rape, re-lived her trauma over and over again to take the case to trial, was bullied and offered no protection by authorities while she patiently waited for justice to be served, and was met with a prosecutor, hilary laborde, that threw in the towel early on the case because it was too similar to a case that she lost in the past, and because jurors "aren't ready to blame rapists and not victims when there isn't concrete proof of more than one victim." her ass backward solution was to offer anderson a plea deal that calls for him to serve three years of probation, pay a $400 fine, and attend counseling. judge ralph strother, who has handed down ridiculously lenient sentences in other sexual assault cases, accepted the plea deal, meaning no jail time, no registering as a sex offender, no justice for the victim. this is the song that never fucking ends. 
if the judicial system is in the hands of people who are not willing to fight for what is right and are willing to enable this behavior to continue, nothing is ever going to change. in fact, this is more of an opportunity for things to get a whole hell of a lot worse. it sends the message that seeking justice as a sexual assault victim is useless, and that rape is completely acceptable. for these people to have the audacity to treat a sexual assault case with such carelessness after the #metoo movement and weinstein case is beyond me, but the last time we spoke up against injustice in the brock turner case, it moved us a little further forward. there's a link in my bio for a petition to remove "judge" ralph strother from the bench. a small step, i know, but still a step forward. #metoosday #getloud #takebackyourpower #rachelriot #wakeupwaco #waco #texas #utdallas

text:
starz female stars and producers on nightmare incidents in the #metoo era
#
a starz tca panel comprised of the network’s leading actresses and series creators tackled the question whether life on set is getting better post #metoo. and while many acknowledge that indeed it is, “it’s the tiny moments” per american gods thespian emily browning that’s still creating confusion. david buchan/shutterstock “i’m sure all of us have a nightmare we heard or experienced, but now there is a space for us to be able to tell those stories. there are certain things i don’t think people can get away with anymore. what’s still kind of evolving, and they’re not nightmare stories — it’s the tiny moments. things that are a little bit ambiguous where a woman automatically feels like ‘did that just happen to me or am i just being sensitive? do i bring this story forward? is it believable or does something worse need to happen?'” explained browning. “that’s where it’s tricky,” said the sucker punch actress, “the tiny moments where we question our sanity.” starz browning’s insight followed on the heels of an experience that vida creator tanya saracho shared: five years ago during her first tv writing gig, she was informed by a male colleague that she was “the diversity hire” in the writers’ room.…
link: http://metoozoo.com/news/starz-female-stars-and-producers-on-nightmare-incidents-in-the-metoo-era/

text:
post credit  @wrapang -  types of rape

date rape: rape committed by someone that the victim is dating. among college students, approximately one-half of all rapes are committed by a date. 
acquaintance rape: rape committed by someone that the victim knows, such as an acquaintance, friend, co-worker, date, or spouse. most rapes are acquaintance rapes.

stranger rape: rape committed by someone that the victim does not know. less than 20 percent of rapes are committed by strangers, although most people believe that stranger rape is the prototypical rape.

alcohol-involved rape: rape in which the perpetrator, the victim, or both are under the influence of alcohol at the time of the incident. 
marital rape: rape committed by the victim's spouse. marital rape often is committed in association with verbal and physical abuse. 
attempted rape: an act that fits the definition of rape, in terms of the strategies used, but does not result in penetration. 
#saynotorape #endrape  #thatlawyerchi k #thisisnotconsent #rapesurvivor #rapecases #womenfightingforwomen #fidaaks #metoo #macfound #unwomen

text: the celebrity brazilian healer joão teixeira de faria aka “john of god” has been indicted for rape and stands accused by hundreds of other women of sexual abuse. he became famous in 2010 when oprah winfrey interviewed him on her talk show. teixeira is famous for performing miracle surgeries which he claimed could cure a wide range of diseases including cancer. bill clinton is believed to have visited him in brazil. after 10 women accused teixeira of abuse on a late night talk show the floodgate opened and another 600 women came forward with additional allegations. teixeira’s own daughter described her father as a monster who raped her from age 10 to 14 at which point he learned she had become pregnant by one of his employees which prompted him to beat her until the point that she had a miscarriage. brazilian activist sabrina bittencourt who had been investigating teixeira claimed “hundreds of girls were enslaved over years, lived on farms in goias, served as wombs to get pregnant, for their babies to be sold.” she went on to say, “these girls were murdered after 10 years of giving birth. we have got a number of testimonies.” the babies who were sold internationally are thought to have brought in up to £40,000 each. because of these allegations bittencourt received death threats and was forced to move out of brazil and live under the protection of international organizations, however she was found dead from a supposed suicide in spain, shortly after. her eldest son confirmed her death, writing on facebook: “she took the last step so that we could live. they killed my mother.” teixeira has been arrested and charged with two counts of rape and two counts of statutory rape.

text:
“the bond with a true dog is as lasting as the ties of this earth will ever be.” - konrad lorenz. 
opening my heart to love is not something i am able to easily do. those people who are close to me would tell you that i have built a wall around my heart. and that’s true, but it is an understatement. i spent too long in a relationship with a man who abused me in every possible sense of the word, and so i have had to learn to protect my heart as a matter of emotional survival. i’ve built a wall. surrounding a fortress. with a moat. filled with sharks and alligators. that are equipped with lasers. i’m an incredibly guarded person. and yet, after everything i’ve been through, and even after losing the love of my life norma jean, i find that all it really takes for me to open my heart to love is a face like this, on a creature within which beats a heart as bruised and misused as my own but just as hopeful and capable of love. cal has been an unbelievable blessing for me, and he’s made me realize much about myself and helped me heal a lot of hurt. i’m so grateful to be privileged to share part of life with him. i love him.
#doberman #dobermanpinscher #adoptme #rescuedog #narcissisticabuse #domesticviolence #domesticabuse #survivor #warrior #cptsd #ptsd #mytruth #speakyourtruth #metoo

text:
what’s holding you back?
.
what happened in your life that is prohibiting you from becoming the person of your dreams?
.
.
why aren’t you where you thought you’d be today?
.
what held me back?
.
.
real talk:
abuse and subsequently the thought that i would never amount to anything. abuse, mental and occasionally physical, instilled in me as a teenager that i had nothing to offer this world. i grew up feeling extremely self-conscious, ashamed of every aspect of myself, and had no self esteem.
.
.
instead of facing my pain and troubles, i ran as far away as i could. i tried to bury the pain and act as though none of it ever happened. i blamed others and played the victim card for many years of my life.
.
. 
i share this with you today because in order for me to reach the next level in my life, i decided that i must be as transparent as possible. no longer am i ashamed of my past.
.
my past taught me so much. it helped me grow. even if you’re living in hell, freedom is just on the other side waiting for you, if you’re willing to learn from the past.
. 
which all leads me to this moment:
.
i quit my job, i am moving overseas, and as a wife and fur mama, i will have a fresh start. i am leaving behind my past not with anger but with gratitude. thank you for all you have taught me. the tears, the anger, the confusion, the loneliness— it was all completely worth it.
.
today, i love harder than i ever have. i forgive, not because i have to but because like others, i too am human and make mistakes. i choose joy, i choose positivity, i choose to rise above in order to give my future self a second chance at truly living. 
if you read this far, thank you. this wasn’t easy to share, but i hope that this helps someone. you aren’t alone. life may feel like hell, but one day you’ll thank those moments for molding you into an even stronger and more resilient person.
.
.
i am my own hero.
.
.
.

pre_proc_tweet:
what’s holding you back?
.
what happened in your life that is prohibiting you from becoming the person of your dreams?
.
.
why aren’t you where you thought you’d be today?
.
what held me back?
.
.
real talk:
abuse and subsequently the thought that i would never amount to anything. abuse, mental and occasionally physical, instilled in me as a teenager that i had nothing to offer this world. i grew up feeling extremely self-conscious, ashamed of every aspect of myself, and had no self esteem.
.
.
instead of facing my pain and troubles, i ran as far away as i could. i tried to bury the pain and act as though none of it ever happened. i blamed others and played the victim card for many years of my life.
.
. 
i share this with you today because in order for me to reach the next level in my life, i decided that i must be as transparent as possible. no longer am i ashamed of my past.
.
my past taught me so much. it helped me grow. even if you’re living in hell, freedom is just on the other side waiting for you, if you’re willing to learn from the past.
. 
which all leads me to this moment:
.
i quit my job, i am moving overseas, and as a wife and fur mama, i will have a fresh sta. i am leaving behind my past not with anger but with gratitude. thank you for all you have taught me. the tears, the anger, the confusion, the loneliness— it was all completely woh it.
.
today, i love harder than i ever have. i forgive, not because i have to but because like others, i too am human and make mistakes. i choose joy, i choose positivity, i choose to rise above in order to give my future self a second chance at truly living. 
if you read this far, thank you. this wasn’t easy to share, but i hope that this helps someone. you aren’t alone. life may feel like hell, but one day you’ll thank those moments for molding you into an even stronger and more resilient person.
.
.
i am my own hero.
.
.
.
  nothume

text:
a lot of people believe we stay because we have nowhere else to go. that was partly true for me. the other part to that is my body was so numb from the physical & mental abuse that i literally don't remember having thoughts or feelings. i knew what i had to do to stay alive & that's all i can remember. it was like a heavy darkness that set in and stayed. •
•
•
•
+++ caution story time +++ there was one and only one time i tried to leave. (unsuccessfully)
i met someone. he was sweet & wanted to rescue me. maybe i had hoped he would as well.
i left "home" and did not come back that night. big mistake.
throughout the night my confidence to leave wore off. it was not time. looking back this night seemed to last forever.
i was dropped back off. 
my choice. 
i knocked on the door. i was greeted by his parents who were pissed. they yelled at me & blamed me for his temper while i was gone. they called me names and sarcastically said they were happy i was back.
i was not allowed to sleep in our bed that night. i was to sleep on the ground. as punishment for leaving he walked on my legs. all night. 
all night 150lbs crushed my legs along with a jump every now and then.
i laid there too scared to move. scared that it would possibly get worse. 
i laid there to survive.
for the next few days i could barely walk. i made up some story naturally because i was embarrassed. 
embarrassed for anyone to know that this was my life. •
•
•
•
++nine years later++
i have been able to start the process of waking my legs up to life. through yoga + running. i'm just starting to realize what has been causing so much pain in my legs. randomly they will hurt. maybe they remember. maybe i am remembering as well 💛💛💛
•
•
•
•
•
•
•

text:
dear bullies 
you see that 15-year-old girl holding hands with her one-year-old son that you called a slut? she was raped at 13. 
you see that boy crying that you made fun of for being a cry-baby? his best friend committed suicide last night. 
you see that girl that you make fun of for having all those bruises? she is abused by her parents. 
you see that bald woman that you made fun of? she is dying of breast cancer. 
you see that old man that you called ugly? he got a serious injury to his face in the war. 
you see that man that you made fun of for having all those burns? he ran into a burning hospital to save his dead daughter. 
you see that boy that you called fat? he is starving himself. 
you see that boy you called stupid? he has down syndrome. 
you see that girl you call fat? she is eating to the point of making herself vomit
you see that girl with the bitch face? she's hiding the girl that was beaten by her last boyfriend.
you see that "problem child acting up"? he's being raped by a family member. 
you see that "tramp doing drugs/drink in a shop door way? he's doing that as its the only way he can survive another night on the street

do you see?? if you dont have anything nice to say dont say anything at all #metoo

text:
on april 16, 2017, in the village of shambhupura in banswara, rajasthan, india, kachru, 21, and monica, 19, got married and were cousins but there family, was not fine with it. the couple were paraded naked, beaten, and sexually assaulted by the whole village of shambhupura and family members including their fathers, brothers and, uncles. the accused have been booked for rioting, wrongful restraint and confinement, wrongly causing hurt, attempted murder, and sexual harassment.
-
-
"the men and children of the village have fled to some other place due to the fear of arrest.
according to the police, on thursday, varaseng resident varanseng resident lord ratna maida, twenty-four-year-old padla resident shankar son lalji, kundelia resident forgotten wife dhulia, resident of shambhupura, gutu son shyama, subhash son hiraji, kangi son kalu, dilip son chetan, ramatu wife kalu and bhusli wife bheema was arrested earlier, nine people including the father of the girl were arrested on wednesday."

text:
𝚆𝚊𝚜 𝚜𝚑𝚎 𝚑𝚎𝚊𝚟𝚎𝚗 𝚏𝚘𝚛 𝚢𝚘𝚞
𝚠𝚑𝚎𝚗 𝚜𝚑𝚎 𝚌𝚑𝚘𝚔𝚎𝚍 𝚋𝚊𝚌𝚔 𝚖𝚢 𝚜𝚌𝚛𝚎𝚊𝚖𝚜
𝚏𝚘𝚛 𝚢𝚘𝚞𝚛 𝚎𝚗𝚓𝚘𝚢𝚖𝚎𝚗𝚝 ?

𝙳𝚒𝚍 𝚑𝚎𝚛 𝚝𝚎𝚊𝚛𝚜 𝚝𝚊𝚜𝚝𝚎 𝚕𝚒𝚔𝚎 𝚑𝚘𝚗𝚎𝚢?

𝚆𝚎𝚛𝚎 𝚝𝚑𝚎 𝚍𝚛𝚘𝚙𝚜 𝚘𝚏 𝚋𝚕𝚘𝚘𝚍 𝚋𝚎𝚎𝚍𝚒𝚗𝚐 𝚊𝚝 𝚑𝚎𝚛 𝚕𝚒𝚙 𝚏𝚛𝚎𝚜𝚑 𝚌𝚛𝚊𝚗𝚋𝚎𝚛𝚛𝚒𝚎𝚜 𝚝𝚘 𝚙𝚒𝚌𝚔
𝚊𝚜 𝚢𝚘𝚞 𝚞𝚗𝚕𝚊𝚌𝚎𝚍 𝚝𝚑𝚎 𝚊𝚜𝚜𝚞𝚖𝚙𝚝𝚒𝚘𝚗𝚜 𝚢𝚘𝚞 𝚠𝚛𝚊𝚙𝚙𝚎𝚍 𝚊𝚛𝚘𝚞𝚗𝚍 𝚑𝚎𝚛 𝚠𝚊𝚒𝚜𝚝.

𝚃𝚎𝚕𝚕 𝚖𝚎 𝚍𝚎𝚟𝚒𝚕, 𝚠𝚑𝚎𝚛𝚎 𝚍𝚒𝚍 𝚢𝚘𝚞 𝚑𝚒𝚍𝚎 𝚢𝚘𝚞𝚛 𝚑𝚘𝚛𝚗𝚜.

text:
[content warning: mentions of sexual assault, sexual harassment, sexual misconduct, transphobia, transphobic violence, homophobia gender and racial discrimination, abortion]⠀
⠀
woman crush wednesday @gloria.allred is a kick-ass civil rights attorney from the us, predominately representing women victims in high-profile sexual assault, harassment or misconduct cases — including in cases against trump, cosby and r kelly, weinstein. she also testified in support of the pro-choice position with norma mccorvey, "jane roe" from roe v. wade, in a 1981 committee hearing on abortion. she represented nicole brown simpson's family during the o. j. simpson murder trial.⠀
⠀
over her extensive career, allred has also fought for farm workers, for gender equality in the workplace, and for gender discrimination against organisations such as the boy scouts and the all-male friars club of beverly hills.⠀
⠀
she was the first recipient of the elgy awards for her work as an lgbtq ally: she fought for the lives and rights of trans women gwen araujo and jenna talackova. she had precedent-setting victories for the rights of gay and lesbian couples to be protected from discrimination from businesses, as well as for victims of aids discrimination.⠀
⠀
allred is currently fighting alongside ohio senators to eliminate the statute of limitations for sexual abuse or assault cases. in 2020, she will represent a woman in a racial discrimination lawsuit against walmart.⠀
⠀
she is the founder and current president of the women's equal rights legal defense and education fund (werldef), the author of "fight back and win: my thirty-year fight against injustice", and the subject of netflix documentary "seeing allred". gloria allred is a damn strong woman.⠀

text:
leah karol’s “for st. agatha of sicily, the martyr”
saint agatha was born around 231 ad. according to the history of the church, she was very beautiful and had many suitors but was determined to never marry and live a contemplative spiritual life. a high-ranking diplomat believed he could force her into marriage but she continually rejected him. he arranged to have her arrested for her profession of christian faith during a time of intense persecution under the roman emperor decius and sat in judgment at her trial. he sentenced her to be imprisoned in a brothel where she was repeatedly raped but bravely continued in her opposition. she was then subjected to horrific acts of torture to the point of having her breasts cut off with pincers, never wavering in her courage and resistance. st. agatha died in prison in 251 a.d. and is revered as a great martyr of the church. she is considered a patron saint of rape victims and breast cancer. #stagatha#renaissancephotography #femalesaints#patronsaint #objectification#groundfloorcontemporary#portraitphotography #saints #patronsaints#pomegranate #breastcancer #metoo#saintagathaofsicily

text:
following the pope’s earlier acknowledgement of sexual misconduct among catholic priests, now us southern baptist is embroiled in similar faith abuse. houston chronicles first published a 3-part report of 700 victims over 20 years. southern baptist convention president j.d. greear has responded in a series of tweets, declaring “we should have been fighting for" victims, and vowing to stop the “predators in our midst.” my learning points:
1. everyone has to beware of the pervasiveness of human sinful nature, in church or outside. it is leaders’ responsibility to ensure various systems are in place to protect the flock. proactiveness will prevent a crisis from happening. in this case, a pastor has sounded the alarm to the convention earlier, but his advice went unheeded. going forward, similar faith abuses could be happening in any denomination, or church, is there sufficient checks and balance in place in your organisation now?

2. excerpts: “lesley wexler, a law professor at the university of illinois, who studies how large institutions react to the #metoo movement’s demands for change, said ...”sometimes institutions reform when massive bad behavior is brought to light and sometimes they don’t,” she said. “if you think about the catholic church and the aftermath of the boston globe reporting, even today we don’t see them being as nearly as proactive as they should be.” “ 
which is why it’s so important to have independent third party checks for accountability, in this case the free press and #metoo movement. they can be used by god to uncover issues that needs to be addressed. they prevent a concentration of power that so easily leads to corruption, because of our sinful nature.

the fear of god is the beginning of wisdom

source: https://www.nbcnews.com/news/us-news/over-200-baptist-ministers-deacons-others-found-guilty-sex-abuse-n970276

text: i am a man, and at times i feel sadness, hurt, vulnerability, and even shame. i also feel strong, masculine, happy, and excited. as men, we have all of these emotions inside of us, and each one of those emotions is as acceptable as the next. true masculinity includes the ability to acknowledge when we are feeling weak, as well as embracing the moments when we feel strong.

text:
second woman accuses virginia lt. governor justin fairfax of 'premeditated and aggressive' sexual assault~usatoday.com

a second woman has come forward to accuse virginia lt. gov. justin fairfax of a "premeditated and aggressive" sexual assault, the latest accusation leveled against him amid calls to resign.

meredith watson said in a statement through her lawyers that fairfax raped her while they were students at duke university in 2000. the accusation follows a previous claim by a former colleague who says fairfax sexually assaulted her in 2004.

fairfax has denied both allegations.

the claims cap off a week of tumult in virginia politics as the state's top three democrats have been embroiled in controversy. the state's governor and attorney general have both admitted to wearing blackface in the 1980s but have rejected calls for them to resign.

in a statement friday, watson's lawyer, nancy erika smith, said fairfax and her client were friends in college but didn't date. 
watson told her friends at the time that fairfax raped her and has provided her lawyers with emails and facebook messages detailing her account of the rape, smith said.

a second woman has come forward to accuse virginia lt. gov. justin fairfax of a "premeditated and aggressive" sexual assault, the latest accusation leveled against him amid calls to resign.

meredith watson said in a statement through her lawyers that fairfax raped her while they were students at duke university in 2000. the accusation follows a previous claim by a former colleague who says fairfax sexually assaulted her in 2004.

fairfax has denied both allegations.

the claims cap off a week of tumult in virginia politics as the state's top three democrats have been embroiled in controversy. the state's governor and attorney general have both admitted to wearing blackface in the 1980s but have rejected calls for them to resign.

in a statement friday, watson's lawyer, cy erika smith, said fairfax and her client were friends in college but didn't date.

text:
resist
.
“an explosion of new activism offers a ray of hope in these dark political times. “ joshua holland the nation
.
in an excellent article by the above journalist, he gives what he calls “your guide to the sprawling new anti-trump resistance movement.” his argument is that although the election of trump was catastrophic for progressive america, the damage might be mitigated over the large term by a remarkable surge of energy on the left in response to the election.
.
as many as 5.2 million people attended women’s marches. senator’s phones were overwhelmed with calls for all kinds of issues from health care to brett kavanaugh. 33% of democrats plan to become more involved in the political process this year because of trump getting elected. people are not happy campers.
.
the article listed of some of the new efforts launched since the election. he said that “not all of them will succeed…but like any collection of innovative start-ups, it only takes a few successes to change the landscape.  this article was  written a year ago, in february 2017.  of the few political operations he listed (indivisible, #knockeverydoor, swing left, run for something ,operation 45,the pussyhat project & movement match) and all but one are still going strong . that’s more than a few.
.
we’ve marched against trump. we’ve marched against guns and for our lives. we marched for the kids in cages. the amazing parkland survivors got teens all over the country involved.  people of influence are speaking out like taylor swift, oprah & diniro. generals and people in high places are expressing their concern.  a record number of women ran for office in 2018 and 256 won house and senate primaries, a huge new record.
.
yes, money plays a huge role in winning elections. but so does shoe leather and good old constituent participation. with rep. alexandria ocasio-cortex getting the youth excited, it’s a relief to know that in spite of all the chaos and subterfuge, some good things are happening. let’s all do our part. resist. then be part of the movement towards a saner future. @blueravenartist
.
facebook @blueravenartist @blueraventees

text:
books: diversity by june sarpong

broadcaster/author june sarpong in an recent interview talked about being excluded from a photo shoot by her then employers mtv, 20 years ago as she was “not suitable for beauty” editorial. her book diversity poses the questions.

could inclusivity be the key to success?

the truth is, inclusion is better for everyone.

in this empowering call to arms, june sarpong # #publishmbe proves why.

putting the spotlight on groups who are often marginalised in our society, including women, ethnic minorities, those living with #disabilities, and the #lgbtq community, diversify uncovers the hidden cost of exclusion and shows how a new approach to how we learn, live and do business can solve some of the most stubborn challenges we face.

with unshakeable case studies, brand-new research from oxford university, and six revolutionary steps to help you overcome unconscious bias, this book will help you become part of a better society.

the old way isn’t working. this is a case for change. ’engaging and informative … highlights our common humanity’ #kofiannan
‘a passionately written polemic’ you magazine

text:
karmele llano, a spanish vet who works in the borneo orangutan survival (borneo, southeast asia), denounced the existence of traffickers who caught female orangutans to force them into prostitution in some countries of asia, according to the spanish newspaper la gaceta.llano reported the discovery of a 12 year old female orangutan named pony, which had been completely shaved, washed, perfumed & even had her lips painted. “pony” was chained to a bed, to make easy & free of incidentals the abuse of the poor animal by the customers of a brothel in a village in central borneo (indonesia) called keremgpangi. they were required 30 state police officers to dislodge the brothel & rescue the animal, who is recovering now in the bangamat river island 1 of the 3 islands used to reintegrate the great apes which have suffered any kind of damage in their contact with humans .
llano asserts that orangutans prostitution has become a common practice in asian countries, especially among workers of logging companies & palm oil plantations, but she warns that it is not the only form of abuse used against orangutans: while female orangutans are tortured & prostituted, the male orangutans are used for boxing shows. in them, the animals are cheered to make them it hit both against the stands as the adversary, while the animator throw them food for every shot that hit the body of the opponent. the training for these shows can include methods such as beatings, deprivation of food, the use of shock weapons & even drugs to make the orangutans work tirelessly.
although we understand these behaviours as uncivilized or characteristic of less-developed countries, the fact is that they also exist in europe. since last year some media have reported the existence of small clandestine brothels in countries like germany & denmark  which are especially devoted to these practices, known as “bestiality brothels” or “erotic zoos, and there are even associations that support bestiality, as zeta. -
#domesticviolence #animalcruelty #rape #animalliberation #freedom #peace #crueltyfree #govegan #bekind #animalsarefriends
#vegansofig#woman#women#explorepage#vegansofinstagram #animal #sex 😡🤬😡🤬

text: i remember that when i was younger, i used to absolutely love school! but as time went on, i found less joy in it. i was constantly under so much pressure, not just from my teachers, but my parents also. of course it is so important to get good grades, but the pressure that is put on teenagers at such a young age is ridiculous, and even scary. for me, social media is my escape from the real world. where i can make my voice heard, opinions known, and speak to other people who feel the same way that i do. something really needs to change in the school system.

text:
good training is not cheap! cheap training is not good! know the difference! don't play yourself 😊👌. find yourself a certified, experienced, knowledge- able fitness coach/ personal trainer who will not only train you physically, but will build/ challenge your mind, will help you pick good lifestyle habits: nutrition coaching, fat loss, increase muscle mass, improved strength, or a whole host of other pursuits.

there is no better testimony as to the quality of a personal trainer/ fitness coach services than one of their already-satisfied clients. that's why potential clients have a duty to do further research when it comes to picking their personal trainer. what represent your personal trainer to you?  what tips/advices can a personal trainer share with his/her clients to get them to be beneficial? 
regardless of the goal, it's a universal truth that exercise alone will never be the answer if the client's mind isn't trained aswell. to help a client get there, a fitness coach needs to find ways to support his/her client in developing healthy behaviours /mindset. 
a certified personal trainer always remember that the word/ definition of "healthy" to him/her might be completely different to his/her client. #fd💪

#personaltrainerwhocares #healthymindsetgoals #qualitytraining #notcheapatall #loveyourself #fitmom #fitat46

text:
this week, the 22s and roe are hosting small group dinners to encourage deeper discussions on the #metoo movement, focused on evaluating widely published cases (weinstein / kavanaugh) as well as recent sexual assault on college campuses. •
here's what the 22s learned!
•
>> listen to and strongly affirm women's experiences with sexual assault, first and foremost
•
>> men should be more proactive in moderating the behavior of their peers (and their own)
•
>> though hard at times, open communication on these issues is essential to shift norms, culture and stereotypes
•
>> high profile controversies played out in the media influence how women process trauma and thus whether they choose to speak up / report
_
we look forward to learning more from our other dinners this week!

#allyship #toolkit #energized #ourwharton #progress

text:
perhaps @erewhonmarket can wake up!!!!!! people want non alcoholic beer like @surrealbrewing !!!!! not everyone wants to get drunk, some people just like the taste of beer but they might be driving or pregnant or on anti depressant or antibiotics and a million other reasons that anywhere you can buy alcoholic beverages you should be required by law to offer an equal non alcoholic option 
meaning that just because i am sober doesn't mean i suddenly stopped enjoying the taste of beer. stop trying to get me to buy your overpriced mocktails and bullshit $9 cbd drinks full of sugar. if i am going to put sugar in my body i want it to taste like beer, i hated cocktails when i was drinking and i hate mocktails when i am sober! 
there are millions of people who are struggling with alcohol and drugs and addiction and they all should have the option to buy non alcoholic beer but the "healthiest" grocery store in america doesn't have it..... instead they are marketing beer to new mothers

text:
as i’m snuggled up to my cup of coffee in my #joy mug, i’m feeling all the warmth and all the love for tomorrow’s #galentinesday talk at the @gtwomanmagazine luncheon. earlier today, i was talking with one of my closest friends and asked her if i should really share a deeper layer of my story during tomorrow’s talk. i shared my fears about being so open and how i didn’t want to over complicate the message. she said a resounding “yes” to more transparency and reminded me that it makes me more relatable. while it feels scary to show more scars than i’m comfortable with, my answer must be a resounding “yes.” i say yes with love for each woman that will be listening tomorrow. for each woman who has been hurt, knocked down or has felt defeated. i will share and i will do it a thousand times again because no one is alone on this journey of life and we need to remember that we have each other and that we can draw upon more love and more strength inside us in order to do #brave things and move from “rock bottom to rocking it.” bring it!, i say. i’m feeling a readiness and a inspiration welling up in me so deeply that all i can do is stand in gratitude. gratitude for my journey and how it has grown me and my perspective on life; gratitude for my tribe - “behind every successful woman is a tribe of other successful women who have her back,” as my dear friend @keciabrick said so beautifully today; gratitude for my children and their courageous lives; and gratitude for the opportunity to speak my truth. with peace and 💕, lindsay
.
.
#writing #writersofinstagram #writer #story #courage #brenebrown #vulnerability #authenticity #wholehearted #wholeheartedliving #counseling #counselor #therapy #therapist #mindfulness #love  #heart #posttraumaticgrowth #transformations #resilience #brave #singlemom #empoweredwomenempowerwomen #singlemom #gtwoman #empowerment #real #metoo #metoomovement

text:
😡•| la ligue du lol |• 😡 .
.
 la ligue du lol était au départ un groupe facebook privé, créé par le journaliste @vincentglad à la fin des années 2000, réunissant « une trentaine de personnes, pour la plupart issues de nombreuses rédactions parisiennes, du monde de la publicité ou de la communication », selon l’article de libération, qui a révélé l’affaire vendredi.

2. si ces harcèlements étaient « publics », pourquoi ne refont-ils surface que maintenant ?

les membres de la ligue du lol aimaient se présenter comme un club de personnalités sortant du lot. « cet endroit réunissait parmi les plus grands talents de twitter de l’époque », plastronne ainsi auprès de libération le podcaster henry michel. le créateur du groupe, vincent glad, théorisait d’ailleurs dès 2009 sur slate.fr la « hiérarchie sociale » s’établissant sur twitter : plus vous êtes suivis, plus vous êtes considérés comme influents, et « au-delà de cinq cents followers, vous pénétrez dans l’aristocratie du réseau ». une position qui a de quoi intimider, raconte aujourd’hui la journaliste @lea_lejeune sur @slate .

3. la culture du « boys club »

l’affaire révèle aussi le manque de diversité dans le milieu de la presse. la coprésidente de l’association des journalistes lgbt, @allezardo déplore dans komitid le manque d’« accès à des postes-clés (…) des minorités sexuelles et racisées » dans les médias mis en cause.
en 2017, la commission de la carte d’identité des journalistes professionnels (ccijp) montre qu'elles sont plus nombreuses aux postes précaires : 
53,5 % de pigistes 
55,7 % en cdd. 
en revanche, elles ne sont que 
38 % aux postes convoités de rédaction en chef  25,9 % dans les directions des rédactions. difficile de ne pas faire de lien entre ces inégalités et les phénomènes de harcèlement, d’autant que des histoires de conversations internes douteuses ont été médiatisées ces derniers jours.

enfin, ces affaires interrogent sur la culture du « boys club », ces groupes d’hommes qui s’organisent pour se répartir les bonnes places et évincer les autres, et prospère bien au-delà du petit microcosme des médias parisiens.

source : @lemondefr
